    feat(mcp-server): expose memory_causal_unlink via the MCP tool registry
    
    The handler (handleMemoryCausalUnlink), lazy-loader, and input schema
    (memoryCausalUnlinkSchema, required edgeId) already existed, but the tool was
    never advertised -- missing from tool-schemas.ts, the context-server runtime
    allow-list, and the causal-tools dispatch -- so it was not callable via MCP.
    
    Wire all three:
    - tool-schemas.ts: add the ToolDefinition descriptor + register it in
      TOOL_DEFINITIONS (which feeds KNOWN_TOOL_NAMES).
    - context-server.ts: add to MEMORY_RUNTIME_TOOL_NAMES (mirrors the siblings).
    - tools/causal-tools.ts: import the handler/type, add to TOOL_NAMES, add the
      dispatch case (parseArgs<CausalUnlinkArgs>).
    
    memory_causal_unlink deletes a causal edge by ID and returns { deleted };
    unknown ids return { deleted: false } without erroring. Update the registry
    test (36 -> 37 tools; expected list + dispatch cases), playbook scenario 049 to
    the now-runnable form, and the README tool counts (36 -> 37 mk-spec-memory,
    61 -> 62 total). Verified via build + static dist import (advertised + routed)
    + the existing causal unit/dispatch suites; live round-trip pending an MCP
    reconnect.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

