Author: MichelKerkmeester <82775228+MichelKerkmeester@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Fri May 29 22:37:50 2026 +0200

    style(spec-kit): enforce sk-code §4 with a comment guard + comprehensive ephemeral-pointer sweep
    
    Add scripts/validation/ephemeral-pointer-audit.mjs — a standalone,
    dependency-free guard that flags ephemeral-artifact pointers in CODE
    COMMENTS only (spec folder/number; T###/CHK-/REQ-/ADR- ids; P0-/P1-/P2-
    and DR-/WS- review-finding ids; #NN issue refs), with precision carve-outs
    for durable look-alikes (HTTP codes, embedding dims, token tiers, V16:
    schema tags, JSDoc @example, runtime path constants, Safeguard #N
    enumerations).
    
    The guard revealed that packet 006 (hand-rolled grep) had cleaned only
    ~10% of the debt: 274 violations across 116 files. This sweep brings the
    whole tree (system-spec-kit + bin) to guard-clean: 261 comment-only fixes
    across 119 files, keeping the durable WHY and dropping only the perishable
    id.
    
    Comment/text only — zero logic change, confirmed by zero dist drift. Both
    @spec-kit workspaces build (tsc exit 0), node --check clean on touched
    .cjs, and the whole-tree guard now exits 0.
    
    Documented as 031-embedding-stack-hardening/007-ephemeral-pointer-guard-and-sweep
    (Level 1, validate.sh --strict exit 0).
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

